    public static class MidiLibrary.Folder
extends Object
implements MidiLibrary.MapNode
    A structure representing a folder in a MidiLibrary. Backed by a TreeMap.

      • validateFolderNames

        protected String validateFolderNames(String folderName,
                                     String parentName)
                              throws InvalidPathException
        Verifies the passed folder and parent names. Override to change acceptable names. This implementation breaks down the path segments of folderName and creates subdirectories.
        Parameters:
        folderName - the requested folder name
        parentName - the fully-qualified name of the parent folder
        Returns:
        the processed folder name
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if folderName is null
        InvalidPathException - if a segment of folderName already represents a non-Folder entry

        public void addChild(@Nullable
                     MidiLibrary.MapNode node)
              throws InvalidPathException
        Adds a MidiLibrary.MapNode to this Folder. If a MapNode with the same name as node already exists and they are both Folders, they are combined; if they are not both Folders, an InvalidPathException is raised.
        Parameters:
        node - the MapNode to be added
        Throws:
        InvalidPathException - if node already exists and both aren't Folders
